This command creates a new file called `index.html` in the current directory. 

Next, you would need to write the HTML code for the page inside this file. The structure of the project would be as follows:

*   `index.html`: This is the main HTML file that contains the structure and content of the webpage.
*   `styles.css`: This is a CSS file that contains the styles for the webpage, including the colors, fonts, and layout.
*   `script.js`: This is a JavaScript file that contains the code for the rotating hexagon and bouncing balls.

Here's an example of what the HTML code in `index.html` might look like:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Rotating Hexagon with Bouncing Balls</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="hexagon">
        <!-- The rotating hexagon will go here -->
    </div>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

And here's an example of what the CSS code in `styles.css` might look like:

```css
.hexagon {
    width: 200px;
    height: 200px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: #f0f0f0;
    position: relative;
}

.ball {
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: #000;
    position: absolute;
}
```

And here's an example of what the JavaScript code in `script.js` might look like:

```javascript
const hexagon = document.querySelector('.hexagon');
let angle = 0;

function drawHexagon() {
    hexagon.style.transform = `rotate(${angle}deg)`;
    angle += 1;
    requestAnimationFrame(drawHexagon);
}

function createBall(x, y) {
    const ball = document.createElement('div');
    ball.classList.add('ball');
    ball.style.left = `${x}px`;
    ball.style.top = `${y}px`;
    hexagon.appendChild(ball);

    function moveBall() {
        x += Math.random() * 2 - 1;
        y += Math.random() * 2 - 1;
        ball.style.left = `${x}px`;
        ball.style.top = `${y}px`;

        if (x < 0 || x > hexagon.offsetWidth) {
            x *= -1;
        }
        if (y < 0 || y > hexagon.offsetHeight) {
            y *= -1;
        }

        requestAnimationFrame(moveBall);
    }

    moveBall();
}

for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
    createBall(Math.random() * hexagon.offsetWidth, Math.random() * hexagon.offsetHeight);
}

drawHexagon();
```

This code creates a rotating hexagon with bouncing balls inside it. The `drawHexagon` function is used to draw the hexagon and update its rotation angle. The `createBall` function is used to create new balls and move them around the hexagon. The balls are created in a loop, so there will be 10 balls moving around the hexagon when the page loads.
